  "texts": [
    "An agent decides whether an element is to be refined based on the current state, i.e., the mesh and solution.",
    "The reward is subsequently defined in terms of the error reduction, which is computed with a ground truth solution.",
    "The trained agent can thus be applied to adaptive mesh refinement to previously unseen simulations.",
    "ExtensionsEach interaction with the environment requires solving the differential equation, which, due to the many interactions, makes reinforcement learning expensive.",
    "The learning can be accelerated through some basic modifications."
